text.section:
No new nor additional evidence may be introduced in the Circuit Court except as to fraud or misconduct of some person engaged in the administration of KRS 95.851 to 95.884 and KRS 95.991, and affecting the order, decision, or determination appealed from, but the court shall otherwise hear the cause upon the record as certified by the board and shall dispose of the cause in summary manner, its review being limited to determining whether or not:
The board acted without or in excess of its powers;
The order, decision, or determination was procured by fraud;
The order, decision, or determination of the board is not in conformity with the provisions of KRS 95.851 to 95.884 and KRS 95.991;
If findings of fact are in issue the party seeking to set aside any order, decision, or determination of the board shall have the burden of proof to show by clear and satisfactory evidence that the order, decision, or determination is unreasonable or unlawful. If upon appeal as herein provided the order, decision, or determination of the board is reversed the party perfecting the appeal shall be refunded by the board his portion of the costs paid for the transcript of the record made on the rehearing.
